main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed near Simiutak, Greenland, for 2-3 hours on 29 October 1953.
interesting points: The objects were described as a white glowing object not moving and another changing colors from red to green to white., The first sighting was noted at 25Z815 and they were under observation for approximately an hour., The report was filed by a radio operator from an aircraft., The sighting occurred during clear weather conditions., The conclusion reached in the report suggested the lights were probably Venus and Vega.
